{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f45ff744-ac51-4c39-82f6-856031c9bc95","content":"Here's the plan and architecture for your RAG-based Q&A feature:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐         ┌──────────────────┐        ┌────────────────┐\n│  Docs/*.md  │──ingest─▶│ Chunking + Embed │──store─▶│ Vector Store   │\n└─────────────┘         └──────────────────┘        └────────────────┘\n                                                            │\n┌─────────────┐         ┌──────────────────┐        retrieve│\n│ User Query  │──POST──▶│  /api/ask        │◀───────────────┘\n└─────────────┘         └──────────────────┘\n                                │\n                         augmented prompt\n                                ▼\n                        ┌──────────────┐\n                        │   LLM (GPT)  │──▶ Grounded Answer\n                        └──────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Key Components\n\n| Layer | Responsibility | Suggested Tech |\n|-------|---------------|----------------|\n| **Ingestion** | Read markdown, chunk by heading/paragraph, generate embeddings | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` + `Markdig` |\n| **Vector Store** | Store/query embeddings | In-process: `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` with an in-memory store (swap for Qdrant/Azure AI Search later) |\n| **Query Endpoint** | `POST /api/ask` — embed the question, retrieve top-K chunks, build augmented prompt | Minimal API or Controller |\n| **Generation** | Send context + question to an LLM, return answer with source references | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` (`IChatClient`) |\n\n---\n\n## Ingestion Pipeline\n\n1. **Load** — read all `Docs/*.md` files at startup (or on-demand via `POST /api/ingest`).\n2. **Chunk** — split each file using markdown heading boundaries; fall back to ~500-token sliding window with ~50-token overlap.\n3. **Embed** — call an embedding model (e.g., `text-embedding-3-small`) per chunk.\n4. **Store** — upsert `{ id, vector, text, source_file, heading }` into the vector store.\n\n## Query Flow (`POST /api/ask`)\n\n1. Embed the user's question with the same embedding model.\n2. Retrieve top-K (e.g., 5) nearest chunks via cosine similarity.\n3. Construct a system prompt: *\"Answer using only the provided context. Cite sources.\"*\n4. Send `[system + context chunks + user question]` to the chat model.\n5. Return `{ answer, sources[] }` as JSON.\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure (proposed)\n\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Docs/                        # existing markdown docs\n├── Models/\n│   ├── DocumentChunk.cs         # id, text, embedding, metadata\n│   ├── AskRequest.cs            # { question }\n│   └── AskResponse.cs           # { answer, sources }\n├── Services/\n│   ├── IngestionService.cs      # load → chunk → embed → store\n│   ├── ChunkingService.cs       # markdown-aware text splitter\n│   └── RetrievalService.cs      # embed query → vector search → top-K\n├── Controllers/\n│   └── AskController.cs         # POST /api/ask, POST /api/ingest\n├── Program.cs                   # DI registration\n└── ProductQA.csproj             # package refs\n```\n\n## NuGet Packages Needed\n\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` — unified LLM/embedding abstraction\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` — vector store abstraction\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.InMemory` — dev/test store\n- `Markdig` — markdown parsing for heading-aware chunking\n\n---\n\n## Considerations\n\n- **Config**: API keys and model names go in `appsettings.json` / env vars.\n- **Scalability**: The in-memory store works for small doc sets; swap to a persistent vector DB via the same `IVectorStore` interface.\n- **Chunk quality**: Heading-based splitting preserves semantic coherence better than fixed-size windows for structured docs.\n- **Observability**: Log retrieved chunk scores to detect poor-confidence answers.\n\nWould you like me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"479b216e-6add-4a27-99c3-932366f166fd","outputTokens":1081,"requestId":"2019:523D2:89115F:9D90B6:6A0531D0"},"id":"d2699518-b357-418b-ba32-b34f1268ab7d","timestamp":"2026-05-14T02:22:32.518Z","parentId":"d1f6e292-4b10-4ac6-b216-a32453760d19"}
